com.igormaznitsa.prol.libraries
Class ProlLibraryWrapper

java.lang.Object
  com.igormaznitsa.prol.libraries.ProlAbstractLibrary
      com.igormaznitsa.prol.libraries.ProlLibraryWrapper

public final class ProlLibraryWrapper
extends ProlAbstractLibrary

This class allows to wrap classes which are non successors of the ProlAbstractLibrary which can be used as prol libraries To sign a method as a predicate you need just to place the WrappedPredicate annotation before it. 

 @WrappedPredicate
  public void helloworld(String str) {
      System.out.println(str);
  }
The ProlLibraryWrapper will make automatic method argument marshaling. It supports primitive types, Strings, arrays, Objects, Map
